Package game

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    Behaviour  
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    Allosaur
    The class to create allosaurs the carnivorous dinosaur that finds and attacks stegosaurs and also will eat any form of meat, including the corpses, eggs and the meat meal kits.
    Application
    The main class for the Jurassic World game.
    AttackAction
    Special Action for attacking other Actors.
    Brachiosaur
    Class for the Herbivore dinosaur Brachiosaur which only eats fruits fed to it and ripe fruits on trees
    BreedingAction
    The action class for the activity of breeding between the dinosaurs
    BreedingBehaviour
    This is the behaviour of the dinosaurs where they actively check if there are suitable targets for the breeding process too occur and whether this actor can breed with another, this checks if there are target that are viable to breed with and whether the target is already pregnant or is a baby
    Bushes
    A class that represents the bushes.
    DeathAction
    action for when the actor dies, it will remove the actor off of the map and add a corpse for the dinosaur of its species on the location that the actor died on.
    DeathBehaviour
    The behaviour class that checks if the conditions for the actor to die has been met, here its whether the actor has been unconscious for over the required number of turns for it to die
    DinoCorpse
    The class for the corpses of the dead dinosaurs, these are food items that are both portable and can be consumed by Allosaur's since its a part of their diet
    Dinosaur
    The general class for all the dinosaurs with functions of common functionality between all the dinosaur species that will be made.
    Dirt
    A class that represents bare dirt and will help check if the dirt can produce a bush every turn.
    DrinkingAction  
    EatingAction
    the class for the action for the dinosaurs to eat food that they have found, it will remove the fruit or food item from the relevant location on the map, if the stegosaur eats a fruit on a bush the fruit will be removed from the bushes list of fruits and if the brachiosaur eats a fruit from a tree the fruit is removed from the list of fruits on the tree in a similar way and if the fruit or food item is on the map and is eated it is directly removed from the map.
    Egg
    The class to create an egg instance of the species of dinosaur that lays it, or bought from a vending machine, it also checks if the egg can hatch and creates a baby dinosaur on the location it hatches, the egg cannot hatch if its in the player inventory.
    FeedAction
    the class for the feeding of a dinosaur by the player, it will heal the amount of food level from the dinosaur corresponding to the food item being fed.
    Fish
    Class for the creation of fish
    FishAction
    the action for the user fishing on the lake
    Floor
    A class that represents the floor inside a building.
    FlyingBehaviour
    The behaviour that adds the capability for a dinosaur to fly once its on the tree and to walk once its fuel runs out and then search and return back to the closest tree to refill its fuel.
    FollowBehaviour
    A class that figures out a MoveAction that will move the actor one step closer to a target Actor.
    FoodItem
    the general class for all the food items that will inherit it, all food items are portable and will have a value that they can heal actors for.
    Fruit
    the class for the fruits being created within the game, a food object that is edible by the herbivores and feed able and portable by the player.
    GrowingAction
    The class that "grows" the input dinosaur.
    GrowingBehaviour
    A class to determine if a dinosaur should grow into its adult form.
    Lake
    Class for the lakes that have fish and sips of water in them
    LayEggAction
    A class for the dinosaurs to lay eggs.
    LayEggBehaviour
    A class to determine if a female dinosaur can lay an egg.
    LazerGun
    class for the lazer gun weapon that the player may own.
    MealKit
    An abstract class that extends from FoodItem.
    MeatMealKit
    A class for a carnivorous meal kit.
    PickFruitBushAction
    A class to pick a fruit from the bush directly.
    PickFruitTreeAction
    A class to pick a fruit from the tree directly
    Player
    Class representing the Player.
    Points
    A class to store the player's points.
    PortableItem
    Base class for any item that can be picked up and dropped.
    Pterodactyl  
    QuitGameAction
    the action for the player to quit the entire game or the game mode that he is playing depending on the game over variable
    SearchBehaviour
    A class that figures out a MoveAction that will move the actor one step closer to a target Actor.
    Sky  
    Stegosaur
    A herbivorous dinosaur called Stegosaur that eats only the fruits on the ground and ripe fruits on the bushes.
    SwitchMap
    The class for the ground item at the top of them map that acts like the border for the player to move between the maps.
    ThirstyBehaviour
    The behaviour of the dinosaur to find a lake to drink from once it gets thirsty with a very low water level this will make the dinosaur follow the closest lake and then drink from it when it is thirsty
    Tree
    A class to create Tree object
    VegeMealKit
    A class for a vegetarian meal kit.
    VendingAction
    class for the vending action that acts as a third party for the player to interact with the vending machine and buy items from what it has in store.
    VendingMachine
    A vending machine class.
    Wall
    A wall class
    WanderBehaviour
    A WanderBehaviour class
  • Enum Summary
    Enum Description
    BreedingStatus
    the enum that adds the capability of the breeding status of the dinosaur, whether or not it can breed or if it is pregnant or not.
    FlyingStatus
    the enum that stated the status of flying of the dinosaur
    FruitStatus
    the status of the fruits that are created, whether they are in players inventory or on a bush or tree or even on the floor.
